        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 6 at 2:45PM CDT until May 6 at 3:15PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>SVRHGX

The National Weather Service in League City has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Trinity County in southeastern Texas...
Northeastern Houston County in southeastern Texas...

* Until 315 PM CDT.

* At 244 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Forest to 7 miles west of Wells to Kennard,
moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Kennard and Weches.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 PM CDT for southeastern
Texas.</instruction>
